Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with 1/2 tsp @salt{} for the pasta.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the tomatoes onto a piece of #foil{}.

Drizzle over some @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and the @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel, then place onto a small #baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, roast the tomato parcel on the top shelf until softened, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the boiling water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{1%pack} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Next, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @water for the sauce{150%ml} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then simmer until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once reduced, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, bring back to the boil, then remove from the heat. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Once cooked, drain the pasta in a #colander{}, then add to the pan of creamy sauce along with the @peas{120%g} and heat through for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

When everything's piping hot, spoon the creamy veg pasta into your #bowls{} and drizzle over the @fresh pesto{32%g}.

Carefully remove your roasted tomatoes from the foil and serve them on top.

Spoon over the tomato juices from the parcel to finish.

Enjoy!